<p>I'm using the code below to delay the loading of a div until the entire web page is loaded. It works perfectly in Firefox and Safari (because they each have lines in the code to make sure it works specifically for each, I haven't tested IE yet), but not in Chrome (which should, I think, work with <code>window.onload</code>).</p>  <p>Could somebody please help me out with this?</p>  <pre><code>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;  function insertFB(){     var html='&lt;div class="fb-page" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/bobcaputolivingwell" data-small-header="false" data-adapt-container-width="true" data-hide-cover="false" data-show-facepile="true" data-show-posts="true"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-xfbml-parse-ignore"&gt;&lt;blockquote cite="https://www.facebook.com/bobcaputolivingwell"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/bobcaputolivingwell"&gt;Bob Caputo Living Well&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';     $("#FB_PAGE").html(html); }  if (document.addEventListener){     document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", insertFB, false); }  if (/WebKit/i.test(navigator.userAgent)){     var _timer = setinterval(function(){         if(/loaded|complete/.test(document.readyState)){             insertFB();         }     },10); }  window.onload = insertFB(); &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>